The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Raymond spins a dull story

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, April 28: The net profit of Raymond Limited was down at Rs 22.90 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2005 compared with Rs 41.33 crore in the year-ago period. Total income has decreased from Rs 338.27 crore in the fourth quarter of 2003-04 to Rs 336.75 crore in the corresponding period in 2004-05.

 ?Profitability was impacted by margin pressures due to increase in input costs, especially that of polyester, cotton and steel, and increases in labour costs, primarily on account of wage settlements,? the company said.

 The company has posted a net profit of Rs 83.15 crore for the year ended March 31, 2005 compared with Rs 132.29 crore in the previous year. Total income has increased from Rs 1125.61 crore to Rs 1211.71 crore.

 The group has posted a net profit of Rs 90.97 crore for the year ended March 31, 2005 against Rs 137.65 crore last year.

 Total income has increased from Rs 1363.29 crore to Rs 1508.92 crore. The board has recommended a 40 per cent dividend on the share capital for 2004-05.

 Godrej Consumer Products 

 Godrej Consumer Products Ltd has posted a net profit of Rs 89.59 crore for the year ended March 31, 2005, up 38.17 per cent compared with Rs 64.84 crore for the year-ago period.

 Total income for the company has increased from Rs 493.79 crore in 2003-04 to Rs 569.08 crore for the year ended March 31, 2005. The board has declared a fourth interim dividend of Rs 5 per share (125 per cent on the shares of the face value of Rs 4 each) for the fiscal 2004-05.

 Varun Shipping

 Varun Shipping Company Ltd has posted a 128 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 81.69 crore for the year ended March 31, 2005 against Rs 35.80 crore in the previous year. The board has recommended a final dividend of 20 per cent.

 Total income from operations for the year ended March 31, 2005 grew to Rs 388.96 crore. 




